### Description

The automatic migration to input signal generate broken code because it adds too many parentheses.

When I run 

```sh
ng generate @angular/core:signal-input-migration --best-effort-mode false --path ./src/app/app.component.ts
```

On this code:

```ts
import {Input} from '@angular/core';

export class MyDirective {

  @Input() public myInput = true;

  public doSomething(): void {
    const foo = this.myInput;
  }
}
```

# Actual

The code is modified like so. And it cannot compile because of the extra parentheses in `this.myInput()();`.

```ts
import {input} from '@angular/core';

export class MyDirective {

  public readonly myInput = input(true);

  public doSomething(): void {
    const foo = this.myInput()(); //  ðŸ’¥  ðŸ’¥  ðŸ’¥ 
  }
}
```


# Expected

Instead I expect to see this result:

import {input} from '@angular/core';

```ts
export class MyDirective {

  public readonly myInput = input(true);

  public doSomething(): void {
    const foo = this.myInput(); //  â¤ï¸ â¤ï¸ â¤ï¸ 
